properties.abstract: When long-distance views are good, the Chasseral-Weissenstein route is one of Switzerland’s most impressive. The tour travels along the southernmost chain of the Jura with views over the entire Mittelland as far as the snow-covered Alps.
properties.description:
About 3 km from the Neuchâtel train station the demanding ascent to Chaumont, the region’s very own mountain begins. A word of advice: those who wish to save energy for later can take the La Coudre - Chaumont funicular. 

The route along the ridge, alternating between south and north side, leads to the border of the Canton Bern. The road then climbs up to Chasseral, the highest peak of the Bernese Jura. The panorama on top, across the Mittelland region and the entire Alpine mountain chain from Säntis to Mont Blanc, is incredible.. Then follows a racy descent to Vallon de St. Imier, before the route enters a gully leading up to Col de Pierre Pertuis. This wide, natural rock tunnel was already used by the Romans as a link from north to south.

From the Col de Pierre Pertuis, the Chasseral-Weissenstein-Bike tour climbs the ridge of the southernmost Jura chain, which it follows up to the Weissenstein above Solothurn. The panorama is breathtaking: far below, the glistening waters of Lac de Neuchâtel, Bielersee and Murtensee, on the horizon the snow-covered Alps, a shimmering backdrop to the densely populated metropolitan area of Bern. Finally, a varied ride through the characteristic Jura landscape of the Thal nature park awaits you. The tour ends in Balsthal. An ideal tour in autumn when thick fog covers the Mittelland and the views from the Jura heights look like something out of a fairytale.
properties.title: Chasseral–Weissenstein Bike
